-- Merkel Said `Dismayed' by Attack That Kills German Soldier in Afghanistan
-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 2010-10-07T15:13:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/merkel-said-dismayed-by-attack-that-kills-german-soldier-in-afghanistan.html
Chancellor Angela Merkel condemned
the “cowardly attack” in Afghanistan that killed one German
soldier and wounded six others, her chief spokesman, Steffen
Seibert, said in an e-mailed statement. Merkel is “dismayed”
about the soldier’s death, the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
